name: bioimmig
label: Generated information on immigration history
description: The BIOIMMIG dataset comprises of a small pool of selected, and mostly generated, variables that deal with questions related to immigrants' migration history in Germany. The thematic areas concern immigrants' reasons for migrating to Germany, living conditions upon arrival, intentions to return to their country of origin, whether they have relatives in the country of origin, expectations for living in Germany and school attendance in Germany.

name: bkbiorki
label: SOEP-RKI Corona study
description: The dataset contains information about: “How many people have already been infected with the coronavirus, SARS-CoV-2? How many infections have gone undetected?” More information about the project can be found online at Nationwide Antibody “Study Living in Germany - Corona Monitoring” (RKI-SOEP). bkbiorki contains results of PCR and DBS tests, as well as survey content. Data on the evaluable PCR and DBS tests are available on request. The case numbers deviate from the method report, since the data set also includes follow-ups and information from persons who did not submit a valid declaration of consent was removed from the data.
description_de:
Der Datensatz enthält Informationen zu: „Wie viele Menschen haben sich bereits mit dem Coronavirus SARS-CoV-2 infiziert? Wie viele Infektionen sind unentdeckt geblieben?“ Weitere Informationen zum Projekt finden Sie online unter Bundesweiter Antikörper „Studie Leben in Deutschland – Corona-Monitoring“ (RKI-SOEP).
bkbiorki enthält Ergebnisse von PCR- und DBS-Tests sowie Umfrageinhalte.
Daten zu den auswertbaren PCR- und DBS-Tests sind auf Anfrage erhältlich. Die Fallzahlen weichen vom Methodenbericht ab, da im Datensatz auch Nachgänge erfasst sind, sowie Angaben von Personen, die keine gültige Einverständniserklärung abgegeben haben, aus den Daten entfernt wurden.

name: hbrutt
label: Initial gross population (first wave, long)
description: The dataset HBRUTT contains field information on the first waves of all surveyed samples (except for samples C and D), both for respondent and non-respondent households. Non-respondent households from first waves can only be found in this dataset. For HBRUTT all cross-sectional variables from HBRUTT$$ are used.
description_de: Der Datensatz HBRUTT enthält Feldinformationen zu den ersten Wellen von allen befragten Stichproben (außer Samples C und D), sowohl für befragte als auch für nicht befragte Haushalte. Nicht befragte Haushalte aus einer ersten Welle sind nur in diesem Datensatz zu finden. Für HBRUTT werden alle Querschnittsvariablen aus HBRUTT$$ verwendet.

name: migspell
label: Migration history
description: MIGSPELL is a dataset in spell-format in which only the population surveyed in the new IAB-SOEP migration sample (Sample M) is included. With the new IAB-SOEP Migration sample, migration history data was collected for the first time. This was done by means of a loop structure in the questionnaire. Two different loops were included: the one aimed at persons born abroad (i.e. migrants) and the one aimed at persons born in Germany. The dataset MIGSPELL was created in order to facilitate the use of this complex part of the questionnaire describing the migration biography of respondents. [A detailed documentation is included in the documentation about biography data in the SOEP.](http://panel.gsoep.de/soep-docs/surveypapers/diw_ssp0266.pdf#page=36)

It contains the Household ID, and never changing individual characteristics, individual weights, as well as the response status, for that individual at each wave, see http://www.diw.de/documents/dokumentenarchiv/17/diw_01.c.432038.de/diw_ssp0150_ppfad.pdf.
